{
  "$schema": "../../../../schemas/workspace/entry_admission_conformance.schema.json",
  "corpus_id": "workspace.project_entry_and_admission.beta",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "Conformance, interoperability, failure / recovery, and switching-parity drill corpus for the M3 project-entry and workspace-admission beta boundary owned by aureline-workspace (build_project_entry_review / ProjectEntryReviewRecord). This manifest is the single source of truth: every positive drill loads one entry review request, builds the review record, requires it to be contract-valid, and matches every expectation below; every negative drill applies a typed tamper to the built record and MUST raise a contract finding containing expected_failure_substring. The corpus proves the M3 entry exit-gate: Open, Clone, Import, Add root, Restore, recent-work reopen, OS-open, CLI-open, and high-authority deep-link rows stay distinct, reviewable, and honest about resulting mode, source-labelled access, first landing surface, destination collision, Blocking now / Recommended soon / Optional later readiness grouping, and deferred work; no entry path silently grants trust, runs setup, executes repo tasks or hooks, auto-trusts, or auto-installs; cross-surface parity preserves the verb and review model, with the deep-link surface always requiring deep-link intent review; failed entry attempts preserve typed inputs, chosen destination, and redacted diagnostics; and credential-bearing source URLs never survive into the built record.",
